abstract.0: Using the latest artificial intelligence and decision science technologies, Oracle Adaptive Intelligent Apps are helping customers benefit from new levels of meaningful business value through Oracle Cloud applications across CX, ERP, HCM, and SCM—without complex and expensive data science expertise. To achieve this, the Oracle Adaptive Intelligent Apps team built a platform to integrate machine learning into Oracle Cloud applications quickly and easily. In this session get an overview of the platform and insight into the roadmap that delivers new features and use cases powered by machine learning across the complete Oracle Cloud application stack.
abstract.1: When the enterprise choses to use IaaS such as Oracle Cloud Infrastructure, four challenges arise: shared responsibility challenges, compliance requirements, data leakage, and misuse of admin privileges. In this session learn how to conquer them with automated security from Oracle CASB Cloud Service.
abstract.2: The roles and responsibilities of today's B2C marketers are constantly shifting to meet the needs of increasingly demanding customers. While each new channel and point of interaction represents an opportunity for growth, these moments can easily be squandered by poorly conceived, disjointed customer experiences. In this session learn more about the future of marketing orchestration and how Oracle Marketing Cloud is innovating and integrating to meet increasingly complex needs of B2C marketing teams.
abstract.3: B2B marketers today are managing more data and using marketing automation and content marketing technology more than ever before, all while striving to bridge the gap with sales teams and ensure the best customer experience. This juggling act can often be overwhelming, and if not managed effectively can result in inefficient sales and marketing processes, lost opportunities, and a lack of personalization needed to drive results. Attend this session to learn more what's next in the world of marketing automation and how to leverage it at your organization.
abstract.4: In this session join AMD to learn more about EPYC 7000 series processors.  Learn about the innovative architecture that allows customers to reclaim budget and costs by lowering TCO through an optimal balance of compute, memory, I/O and advanced security features. Ideal for general purpose infrastructure and virtualization on-premises and in the cloud. Plus see a glimpse of some exciting new AMD products.
abstract.5: When information is delivered in the context of a key business role or process, there is immediate understanding.  However, it’s more than contextual information—it’s about key performance indicators to manage performance, exploring drivers of performance, and leveraging machine learning to enhance your understanding that leads to timely action for optimal impact. In this session learn about Oracle’s strategy, products, and plans for next-generation analytics applications based on Oracle’s SaaS application suite, as well as where these applications are headed in the future.
abstract.6: Oracle has produced game-changing results for customers with its latest PeopleSoft applications and PeopleTools.  In this session hear how Oracle plans to further increase the value of the applications by adopting key technology innovations. See what is next for PeopleSoft Fluid User Interface, Oracle’s full suite of cloud-ready lifecycle management tools, simplified analytics, and more. Oracle’s strategy is to continue to extend the value of your PeopleSoft investment.
abstract.7: Autonomous databases change the security game. With autonomous handling of basic security processes such as patching, encryption, and auditing, security administrators are now free to concentrate on higher-value security tasks. This session walks you through the default security controls provided by Oracle Autonomous Database Cloud and then dives into where you should focus to take your database security to the next level.
abstract.8: In the past two years, AI technologies have transformed the way we interact with systems and devices across channels. Chatbots have become widely adopted, and Oracle has started to evolve them into digital assistants that can complete user tasks. A digital assistant is able to leverage AI to make recommendations, possess many skills, initiate conversations, and use cognitive services to provide an ambient human experience. In this session see how Oracle Digital Assistant can transform enterprises with next-generation conversational AI technologies.
abstract.9: ARM is becoming more and more popular as an alternative to x86 architecture. Oracle works closely with industry-leading partners to enable tested, certified, and supported solutions for Oracle Linux and virtualization customers. With an extensive ecosystem, customers can improve time to market and simplify deployment. In this session learn from Oracle and its partners how to build an ARM64-based solution that makes sense for your business.
abstract.10: This Oracle development session provides an overview of Oracle E-Business Suite technology strategy, capabilities, and associated business benefits of recent releases and roadmap. Learn about the latest technology for running Oracle E-Business Suite on-premises or in the cloud.  Hear about new usability enhancements and mobile applications, systems administration and configuration management tools, and security features and tools for extending and customizing Oracle E-Business Suite and external integrations.
abstract.11: The migration to the cloud and new technologies such as VR, robotics, and Blockchain have generated fundamental shifts in how customers/employees/partners engage with ERP/SCM/HCM/CX applications. Digital enterprises must now meet the new demand for application engagement while maintaining a proliferating footprint of SaaS and on-premises applications such as Oracle E-Business Suite, and Oracle’s PeopleSoft and JD Edwards. A modern innovative cloud platform is paramount for business and IT to deliver differentiated experiences quickly and at lower cost. Join this session to see how companies can benefit from Oracle Cloud Platform Services to connect data, extend experiences, and gain insight across applications, with AI/machine learning–powered intelligence.
abstract.12: In this session see the evolution of Oracle CPQ Cloud Service and learn how feature requests are prioritized to stay ahead of the CPQ marketplace. Oracle's goal is to further enable customers' success with functionality that drive sales efficiency, simpler administration, greater flexibility, and performance at an ever-increasing scale.
abstract.13: How do you plan your big data journey in the age of the cloud? How do you start to transition from on-premises to the cloud? How do you go to the cloud but deal with data locality rules, GDPR, and the like? All these questions are answered in this session. Hear comprehensive strategies and solutions for your cloud journey to big data benefits. Learn about Oracle’s unique offering: a functionally equivalent on-premises, cloud at customer, and public cloud stack that makes any hybrid strategy feasible out of the box. Discover solutions combining these offerings to your best strategic fit, whether this is hybrid, working on development and testing in public cloud, or running a full cloud stack but on your premises.
abstract.14: In this session learn about what’s next for customer platforms that are lower cost, less risk, and more agile, as well as Opower solutions that offer dependable results at scale. See how Oracle is expanding the scope of customer information systems and providing SaaS solutions of the future, as well as the latest innovations in UX/UI, analytics, and operational efficiency. The session also explores what's next for Opower solutions, including solar customer engagement and behavioral load shaping.
abstract.15: Oracle Databases in the Oracle Cloud offer a high degree of security. Secure infrastructure, data encryption by default, and automated patching all help to keep data safe from a variety of threats.  However, understanding the risks associated with data, controlling access to it and monitoring its use are customer choices, making security a shared responsibility between the customer and the cloud provider. Oracle Data Security Cloud Service is a unified control center for managing data security in Oracle Databases in the cloud. It allows you to quickly understand the sensitive data in your care, evaluate configuration risks, enable auditing and detective controls, mask data for use in test and development environments, and more. This session provides an overview of the Data Security Cloud Service and takes attendees through a full end-to-end scenario of how they can protect data in Oracle Databases. No prior security experience is needed.
abstract.16: Whether you use the term virtual assistant or chatbot, new automated conversational technologies are changing the way customers engage. In this session discover the new virtual assistant for Oracle Service Cloud, including a solution overview and roadmap.
abstract.17: This session highlights new product innovation and enhancements that are delivered in the latest Oracle’s JD Edwards EnterpriseOne releases, providing insight to help your organization map a meaningful business strategy in today’s connected, agile, and real-time businesses.  Learn how JD Edwards is the platform for competing in a digital economy.
abstract.18: How do you manage development across multiple cloud services? How do you get a real-time view of the artifacts that make up your complete application and their lifecycle? How do you track multiple environments (dev/test/prod)? How do you prioritize your team's work and make sure they have the infrastructure they require? In this session meet the next version of Oracle's solution-driven development team hub, a centralized location where you can manage and track all your cloud development activities.
abstract.19: For organizations that aspire to be AI-driven, it is critical to develop standardized practices for deploying predictive models into production, as well as monitoring and managing those models. While some teams may overlook this process in the early stages of their data science maturity, it is essential to lay the right ModelOps foundation so that your organization can efficiently scale from deploying and managing tens of models to hundreds or thousands. In this session learn how organizations can develop best-in-class ModelOps practices, and leverage Oracle’s data science platform to shorten time to deployment and ensure that models are continuing to deliver accurate predictions after deployment.
abstract.20: The definition of strategic workforce planning will vary depending on who you are and your role.  In addition, the evolution of modern strategic workforce planning provides a new definition as well as new expectations of teams to collaborate. This session explores the evolving best practices and the expectations of HR and finance practitioners to meet strategic workforce planning needs.
abstract.21: Take your Unicode migration project to the next level with Oracle Database Migration Assistant for Unicode and new machine learning–based techniques. In this session discover upcoming new features of Oracle Database Migration Assistant for Unicode, including machine-assisted character set detection for enhanced accuracy in data cleansing as well as automated discovery of common latent application issues that need to be addressed along with the data migration. In addition, get tips and best practices for implementing a scalable and repeatable Unicode migration solution for Oracle Databases.
abstract.22: Bots are the future. In fact, if you're wondering today whether your business should create a bot, you’re asking the wrong question. In this session see a case study on how an enterprise benefits from a digital assistant. OneBot is designed to support and help employees on their daily professional life, be it onboarding, HR queries and activities, IT help, meeting scheduling, or just simply booking their timesheets globally in different languages. Hear about design patterns and implementation guidelines in bot development and API architecture.
abstract.23: Oracle’s PeopleSoft continues to introduce new and powerful analytic and reporting capabilities. In this session learn about newly introduced features as well as plans for the future of reporting and analytics.  Discover how you can take advantage of analytics in conjunction with other PeopleSoft features such as related information, dashboards, and search to provide richer business insight and valuable decision support where it matters most.
abstract.24: Oracle invested a lot of resources to simplify PeopleSoft environment management in the Oracle Cloud.  In this session learn how PeopleSoft’s cloud manager helps maximize efficiency and reduce the effort it takes to provision and maintain application environments. Find out how PeopleSoft PeopleTools patches and upgrades have been completely automated. This session also highlights all the features of the cloud manager, as well as discussing some of the future enhancements currently being evaluated. If you want your PeopleSoft applications to thrive on the Oracle Cloud, this session is for you.
abstract.25: The flexibility and extensibility of Oracle's PeopleSoft differentiates it from other products. Now you can meet unique requirements while eliminating or isolating costly customizations. Make changes the right way to minimize impact on your lifecycle. In this session learn how personalization can lead to greater adoption and productivity and see how to provide a user experience tailored to your users and business needs. Learn about PeopleSoft tools and frameworks such as event mapping, page and field configurator, and navigation collections that enable you to align your PeopleSoft system with your enterprise.
abstract.26: Advances in Oracle’s PeopleSoft’s cloud manager have improved the experience of running your selective adoption processes from the Oracle Cloud.  In this session explore how Oracle Cloud Infrastructure can be leveraged to streamline the way you apply maintenance.
abstract.27: Tremendous advancements have been made in Oracle’s PeopleSoft user experience since the introduction of PeopleSoft Fluid User Interface, providing customers with a contemporary, intuitive, and mobile platform. This session describes how to bring together the latest changes in a way that's most beneficial to your enterprise and users.  Learn how to best employ PeopleSoft Fluid User Interface, the classic plus styling, clustering, and other new features.  Discover what's on the horizon for the PeopleSoft user experience.
abstract.28: This session presents Oracle’s product strategy for procurement, a critical function that prioritizes customer service to help it exert influence over behavior in the organization. Spanning supplier, cost, and value, procurement can connect enterprise requirements to sourcing decisions and order execution.  Procurement can ensure compliance even during innovation, operating as a business partner to drive joint success with stakeholders as enterprise priorities evolve. Learn how recent features benefit critical business processes and what lies ahead on the product roadmap. This is the cornerstone session for Oracle E-Business Suite customers interested in improving the procurement, sourcing, and finance functions.
abstract.29: Oracle Essbase, available as part of Oracle Analytics Cloud, brings scenario-building, "what if" applications, and rapid collaboration on shared analytic tasks to life with data from within and outside your enterprise.  In this session see what Oracle Essbase can do for your organization, learn about the new capabilities recently introduced with the latest release, and explore innovative ways to create and manage Oracle Essbase applications. Also hear about what's in store for Oracle Essbase in the near future. It's an exciting time for Oracle Analytics Cloud and Oracle Essbase—forecasting business scenarios has never been faster or easier.
abstract.30: With data and analytics driving virtually everything you do, you need to know where Oracle Analytics Cloud can take you next. In this session join the Oracle Analytics team to see the latest innovation in Oracle Analytics Cloud’s service capabilities including data preparation and visualization, machine learning, natural language, big data, Oracle Essbase, and more. This information will assist you to plan your next steps and take full advantage of analytics in the cloud as a catalyst for innovation and transformation.
abstract.31: Oracle Application Development Framework is a productivity enhancing framework for the development of enterprise Java applications. In this session learn about the latest features, how Oracle Application Development Framework can benefit from the cloud, and how Oracle Application Development Framework can be used in combination with new UI technologies.
abstract.32: Looking for a better way to run your critical enterprise applications? Oracle Cloud Infrastructure has an ever-expanding range of capabilities to make it easier than ever to move and improve existing applications and build new ones on the same high-performance platform. In this session explore the fundamentals and learn how to gain IT agility without sacrificing predictability and control. Get an update on some awesome new cloud offerings to help you migrate apps, host blazing fast databases, run intensive machine learning and HPC workloads, and build container-native, production-grade services. And get a preview of where we're going next.
abstract.33: In this session learn about important new features and innovation themes driving the Oracle Commerce Cloud roadmap.
abstract.34: In this session learn how Oracle Content and Experience Cloud provides a platform for experience assembly, governance, and transformation where customers can build and orchestrate world-class customer experiences. Hear about Oracle’s vision and strategic approach in this highly interactive session involving various in-market and in-progress tools spanning an enterprise-class API-first CMS, an experience factory to govern and scale thousands of mission-critical experiences, and advanced machine learning tools to create smart content. Learn to orchestrate personalized consumer journeys from sales to service to lifelong brand loyalty.
abstract.35: Oracle Database In-Memory is the industry-leading in-memory database technology, accelerating analytics by orders of magnitude as well as improving hybrid OLTP applications. This session provides an overview of the dual-format technology underlying Oracle Database In-Memory and the features that enable analytic processing speeds of billions of rows per second. Learn about the innovations in Oracle Database 12c Release 2, as well as new features introduced in Oracle Database 18c such as automatic in-memory, in-memory optimized arithmetic, and many more performance enhancements.  This session also includes a preview of the future roadmap for this groundbreaking in-memory technology.
abstract.36: A critical step in becoming a data-driven organization is to make data accessible. Oracle Data Catalog is a next-generation data catalog that unlocks the data capital in an enterprise. In this session learn how Oracle Data Catalog enables analysts/data scientists to find relevant data, data engineers to democratize data access, and data stewards to curate.
abstract.37: This session highlights a brand new Oracle cloud service feature: Oracle Data Catalog. Oracle Data Catalog enhances the transparency, traceability and trust in enterprise data assets in the Oracle cloud and beyond, enabling efficient and governed data exploitation for competitive advantage. Learn how Oracle Data Catalog can discover, organize, enrich, and trace enterprise data assets across the hybrid landscape. See a demonstration of Oracle Data Catalog and get details on the product roadmap and vision for a single data catalog for Oracle and other enterprise data assets.
abstract.38: Oracle Digital Assistant, formerly known as Oracle Intelligent Bot, gained rapid customer adoption since its introduction a year ago. New features such as QnA Service, Live Agent Chat Integration, and many others were introduced rapidly as the solution evolved from an enterprise chatbot to a complete digital assistant platform. In this session learn the strategy and roadmap for Oracle  Digital Assistant and how it will power the next wave of innovation in enterprise systems.
abstract.39: Come to this session to learn about new advanced analytics solutions for Oracle E-Business Suite SCM customers. Learn how Oracle Inventory Management and Oracle Warehouse Management can predict whether you will deliver shipments on time and give you recommendations to fix fulfillment scheduling issues. Learn how Oracle Service Cloud and Oracle Enterprise Asset Management provide an integrated approach that can help you progress from a reactive to a predictive and prescriptive organization. By performing advanced analysis of the data in your Oracle E-Business Suite system, these solutions provide actionable insights and real-time recommendations that help you increase profitability and margins, optimize operational costs, reduce overhead, and maximize supply chain efficiencies.
abstract.40: What does digital transformation mean for procurement and projects? Technological advances are changing and disrupting our everyday lives, enabling you to disrupt, transform, and innovate your business model. In this session learn how Oracle E-Business Suite's strategy can help you differentiate your organization and drive new business outcomes. And hear firsthand how a large global construction industry customer is using these innovative applications to execute a digital transformation project that will disrupt 50 years of industry best practices.
abstract.41: Companies in asset-intensive industries know that enterprise asset management is a cornerstone of operational excellence. Learn how Oracle Enterprise Asset Management provides an integrated approach that can help you progress from a reactive to a predictive organization while helping you achieve operational excellence. This session gives an overview of Oracle Enterprise Asset Management, its roadmap, and the latest features.
abstract.42: This session provides an overview of Oracle’s product strategy for Oracle E-Business Suite Financials. The session covers the capabilities and associated business benefits of recently released features. There is a focus on themes for future releases of the product roadmap as well as the capabilities planned. This is a must-attend session for Oracle E-Business Suite Financials customers.
abstract.43: In this session representatives from Oracle E-Business Suite’s HCM development executive management share their vision, key focus areas, and roadmap for the product line. They also highlight key new features and capabilities added to the product line in recent times.
abstract.44: In this session representatives from product development talk about features that will make your payroll and benefits administrators' lives easier as well as reduce costs. Learn about new payroll and benefits features such as consolidating payees for third-party payment processing, providing form 1095-C online, as well as adding a new W-2 signup page via self-service HR and a whole lot more.
abstract.45: Whether you’re servicing your customer's assets or maintaining your own, you’re constantly looking at how best to automate processes while maintaining the digital thread.  Come to this session to learn how Oracle Service Cloud and Oracle Enterprise Asset Management provide an integrated approach that can help you progress from a reactive to a predictive and prescriptive organization. Learn how Oracle E-Business Suite service and maintenance customers can harness the power of connected devices, predictive insights, and recommendations. See how these predictive outcomes can be leveraged to augment business processes to achieve fully autonomous operations and maximize uptime.
abstract.46: The Oracle Exadata architecture is being transformed to provide the world's most advanced cloud and in-memory functionality for both online transaction processing and analytics using remote direct memory access, dynamic random-access memory, nonvolatile memory, and vector processing. This session provides an overview of current and future Exadata capabilities, including disruptive in-memory, public cloud, and Oracle Cloud at Customer technologies.
abstract.47: In this session learn how Oracle Financials Cloud empowers customers to thrive in the digital economy. See highlights of Oracle’s continuous investment in new features to deliver service excellence, expand global and industry capabilities, and create modern, agile finance through innovation. This session also previews Oracle’s roadmap for emerging technologies in financial applications.
abstract.48: Oracle Forms 12c (12.2.1.3) introduced you to forms application deployment services (FADS).  FADS gives you the ability to package and deploy applications similar to how a Java 2 Platform, Enterprise Edition application might be deployed.  In this session learn how the power of FADS along with Oracle Developer Cloud Service can become the perfect marriage. Bring application lifecycle management to your Oracle Forms applications and deliver applications and their updates faster than ever before.
abstract.49: In this session learn how Oracle HCM Cloud’s payroll solution is moving ahead with increased country coverage for payroll and payroll interface.
abstract.50: Developing and retaining talent is a top priority for business leaders. Having the right tools to manage your talent, as well as for your employees and managers to use in everyday productive work is key.  Oracle continues to focus its energies to support these vital employee business processes, and to enhance the functionality and user experience to meet the demands of today's modern workforce. In this session learn about customer and market drivers, hear about the latest features in Oracle’s talent management suite, and discover Oracle’s investment priorities as it continues to support customers moving forward.
abstract.51: Oracle Procurement Cloud solutions continue to evolve and offer new capabilities to enable modern procurement practices. In this session learn how customers have adopted Oracle Procurement Cloud and hear how planned improvements to sourcing, contracting, self-service procurement, purchasing, and supplier management can help deliver value to your organization.
abstract.52: Oracle Project Portfolio Management Cloud solutions are continually innovating with new functionality and capabilities to drive your modern project management success. In this session learn how customers have adopted Oracle Project Portfolio Management Cloud, and see how planned improvements to project financial management, project execution management, mobile, social, and industry-oriented enhancements will positively impact your projects and resources, and deliver project value to your organization.
abstract.53: The session provides an overview of Oracle’s product strategy for Oracle Projects. Learn about the capabilities and associated business benefits of recently released features. There is a focus on themes for future releases of the product roadmap as well as the capabilities planned. This is a must-attend session for Oracle Projects customers.
abstract.54: Oracle Real Application Clusters (Oracle RAC) has an impressive record of innovation over the past 20 years. Oracle Database 18c is now providing the innovation for Oracle RAC to become a key technology in Oracle’s cloud as well as Oracle Autonomous Database Cloud. Attend this unique and innovative session brought to you by Oracle development for a glimpse of Oracle RAC’s road ahead and a detailed discussion on how to use the latest features in Oracle RAC to optimally benefit from future developments.
abstract.55: Following on the exciting announcement that Oracle had launched a new recruiting product natively built within Oracle HCM Cloud, attend this session to join a discussion on the latest technology progression of Oracle Recruiting Cloud Service. Get an update on product strategy, a review of what is to come in the roadmap, and insight into customer adoption and results.
abstract.56: With the increased desire and drive to move to the cloud comes the need for a clear path to help retailers transition to and meet the demands of this modern and ever-evolving world of retail. In this session get a detailed walkthrough of a blueprint to the cloud at Oracle Retail.
abstract.57: This session explores Oracle Enterprise Data Quality, Oracle’s strategic platform for data profiling, parsing, standardization, and matching, enabling best practice data governance, data integration, analytics, and master data management, both on-premises and in the cloud. This session provides an overview of the product, and explains how Oracle is investing in simplifying the journey to high-quality, trusted enterprise data. Learn about key customer deployments and understand the product roadmap and strategy for data quality and data governance.
abstract.58: Oracle GoldenGate has been the market leader in the area of data replication and real-time data integration for the past two decades. Customers have leveraged Oracle GoldenGate to solve various use cases ranging from active-active, real-time data warehouse, data migration, and big data integration for both cloud and on-premises. Join this session led by Oracle product management to hear about the key new features of Oracle GoldenGate including platform, streaming analytics, big data, and cloud.  This session also provides a glimpse into the future product strategy and roadmap, and includes a customer use case and how it solved its challenges with Oracle GoldenGate.
abstract.59: This session explores the range of solutions in Oracle’s data platform. Get an overview and roadmap for each product, including Oracle Data Integrator, Oracle GoldenGate, Oracle Metadata Management, Oracle Enterprise Data Quality, and more. Learn how each solution plays a role in important cloud and big data trends, and discover a vision for data integration now and into the future.
abstract.60: This session provides an overview of Oracle’s data platform as well as a detailed look into Oracle Data Integrator, Oracle’s strategic product for batch data integration via extract-load-transform processes on-premises or in the cloud. Get a product overview and learn about future product strategy, particularly Oracle Data Integrator’s latest capabilities with improved support for big data and cloud technologies and deployments, and lifecycle management. The session also features a customer presenting their experience in using Oracle’s data platform and Oracle Data Integrator with Oracle Autonomous Data Warehouse Cloud. Attendees gain valuable knowledge and insights for their own cloud adoption plans.
abstract.61: In this session see the evolution of Oracle Service Cloud. Learn about some of the exciting new features and innovations coming in Oracle Service Cloud.
abstract.62: Come to this session and hear from product executives about the latest strategy, vision, and roadmap for Oracle Mobile Platform, a part of Oracle's multichannel cloud platform. Hear how Oracle Mobile Cloud Service has evolved into a true multichannel platform and learn how Oracle is taking mobile application development to new heights with the latest innovations around augmented reality, advanced notifications, crash analytics, and more. For current Oracle Mobile Cloud Service customers as well as for anyone interested in the latest mobile innovations, this is a session that can't be missed.
abstract.63: Oracle Solaris and SPARC technologies are developed through Oracle’s unique vision of coengineering operating systems and hardware together with Oracle Database, Java, and enterprise applications. Discover the advanced features that secure application data with less effort, implement end-to-end encryption, streamline compliance assessment, simplify management of virtual machines, and accelerate performance for Oracle Database and middleware. In this session learn how SPARC/Solaris engineered systems and servers deliver continuous innovation and investment protection to organizations in their journey to the cloud, see examples of cloud-ready infrastructure, and learn Oracle's strategy for future enhancements for Oracle Solaris and SPARC systems.
abstract.64: In this session hear from the Oracle Student Cloud team to understand the strategy for providing the practical path for customers wanting to modernize their student solutions. Explore the breadth of the Oracle Student Cloud solution today, from student recruiting to student management and financial aid, and review the roadmap. See how the student management solution provides a new and innovative architecture and user experience, complemented by the extreme automation and personalization of the student financial planning module, designed to support modern education models. If you’re interested in what Oracle has delivered to modernize the core business of higher education and support student success, join us for this session.
abstract.65: In this session learn how to maximize your talent acquisition success with Oracle Talent Acquisition Cloud (formerly Taleo Enterprise Edition).  In this session get a comprehensive update on Oracle's vision, product strategy, and roadmap investments. Topics covered include recent innovations and a look ahead to upcoming investments that will serve candidates, hiring managers, and your recruiting organization.
abstract.66: Oracle WebLogic Server is the leading platform for enterprise Java applications. Oracle Coherence sets the standard for in-memory data grids. In this session learn about the latest features for deploying and integrating applications running on traditional systems, in Docker and Kubernetes, and/or in Oracle Cloud. Learn about application development, management, disaster recovery, Kubernetes support, Oracle Java Cloud Service, Oracle Application Container Cloud Service, microservices integration, and more. The session also discusses plans for upcoming releases supporting Java Platform, Enterprise Edition 8, and provides an update on the road forward for Java EE technologies in the Jakarta EE platform for cloud-native applications.
abstract.67: In this session hear about the strategy for Oracle’s ongoing investment in PeopleSoft.  Understand the drivers behind the hundreds of new features and enhancements delivered in the current PeopleSoft offering and learn about the enhancements currently in development and planned for the PeopleSoft roadmap.  Discover how Oracle is embracing continuous delivery to provide new innovations to customers on an ongoing basis, and how every PeopleSoft customer can engage with Oracle to impact the roadmap, help prioritize investments, and collaborate with the PeopleSoft community.
abstract.68: At the core of Oracle’s PeopleSoft HCM application suite lies an abundance of functionality that caters to the functional HR administrator, whose chief responsibility is to maintain an accurate system of record for the organization. This session explores core HR functionality such as regulatory and legislative changes, modernization of position management and profile management, work centers and navigation collections, simplified analytics, onboarding, and other tools that are available to make the lives of HR administrators easier.
abstract.69: Attend this session to get an update of continuous innovations within Oracle's PeopleSoft Financials that support collaboration between business and financial operations, expanded visibility, and simplifying business flows. Learn how PeopleSoft Financials expands value to your organization’s stakeholders to improve productivity, empower users with new reporting power to make timely bottom-line decisions, and reduce costs of operations through new technologies. This session also showcases the roadmap for PeopleSoft Financials, including the delivery of PeopleSoft Update Images to support continuous collaboration and productivity for your organization’s business growth.
abstract.70: This session provides an update of the latest features available for Oracle's PeopleSoft human capital management (HCM) solutions, including the latest developments in core human resources, payroll, time and labor, learning and talent management, and benefits. Learn about recently delivered features and upcoming functionality such as regulatory and legislative changes, modernization of administrative pages, customer-requested enhancements, and new HCM  frameworks for extensions without customizations.  The session also explores what successful customers are doing with their PeopleSoft HCM solutions including deploying fluid, self-service capabilities to advance the effectiveness and usability of their PeopleSoft system.
abstract.71: In this session discover the key investment areas in Oracle’s PeopleSoft procurement solutions. Learn about specific new and planned features for PeopleSoft's procurement applications and how they can help increase efficiency, improve user adoption, and improve the bottom line. See how to increase user adoption utilizing PeopleSoft Fluid User Interface for improved usability, achieve time efficiencies and bottom-line savings with the PeopleSoft’s supplier lifecycle management solution, and automate compliance and reduce spend with integrated sourcing and contract solutions.
abstract.72: This session is a one-stop shop for those interested in the latest solutions available in Oracle’s PeopleSoft talent management suite of applications including PeopleSoft ePerformance, PeopleSoft Enterprise Learning Management, PeopleSoft Recruiting solutions, and PeopleSoft Compensation Mart. See product demonstrations of new capabilities available for employee snapshot, total rewards statement, and compensation history that are all part of the core HR license. This session also covers how to maximize your investment in PeopleSoft by leveraging the power of profile management and the new fluid capabilities available.
abstract.73: In this session learn about the latest solutions delivered and planned updates for Oracle’s PeopleSoft workforce management applications including payroll for North America, time and labor, absence management, and benefits administration. Many expected changes are driven by legislative and regulatory changes in the US and Canada. Hear about new functionality currently under development and what's next on the roadmap. Learn about all the capabilities planned including benefits open enrollment, timesheet entry, and work center, designed with the payroll clerk in mind as a one-stop shop for processing and managing payroll every cycle.
abstract.74: Artificial intelligence technologies increasingly filter into everyday lives to enhance and improve experiences in different ways. In the same way, AI is  changing the behavior of the workplace and driving meaningful business transformation. In this session learn about Oracle's artificial intelligence and data-driven apps, Oracle Adaptive Intelligent Apps, ready-to-go packaged apps built on Oracle’s modern cloud infrastructure for scalability and security. Oracle Adaptive Intelligent Apps utilize trusted data, pretuned algorithms, and cutting-edge decision science to connect insights and deliver better outcomes across sales, marketing, service, commerce, enterprise resource planning, and human capital management.
abstract.75: Retailers need to meet at the corner of innovation and intent to attract new customers, maintain loyalty, and preserve profits. In this session get a detailed look at recent innovations and a forward look into Oracle’s plans across the retail portfolio. See points of integration and collaboration across the full Oracle offerings for retail.
abstract.76: It's been an incredibly busy year for Oracle’s Database Security team, with the new Oracle Data Security Cloud Service, Oracle Database Security Assessment Tool, and Oracle Key Vault with multimaster support. The European Union's General Data Protection Regulation (EU-GDPR) is now in effect as well, and efforts to comply have started. In this session learn what the team is working on this year to help you comply with latest regulations, and how to secure your databases whether on-premises or on the cloud.

With Oracle’ ESP maturity model, companies have the ability to objectively engage the enterprise to develop roadmaps to align their capabilities with the business strategy and customer expectations. In today’s competitive and fast-changing markets, these roadmaps must be practical, innovative, and ultimately transformational.  In this session learn about this compelling framework.
abstract.78: Windows Server 2016 introduced native container support that allowed Windows developers to take advantage of the many benefits of Docker containers, including ease of deployment, consistency, scalability, and platform flexibility. This session includes demos showing how to configure and use Oracle Database, Oracle Database Instant Client, and .NET  libraries with Docker for Windows. Get detailed info on supported configurations, known issues, and Docker Hub.
abstract.79: In this session attendees learn how Oracle’s Siebel CRM is a core component of the CX product suite, with best-of-breed product solutions and a rich innovation roadmap.
abstract.80: Integration plays a crucial role in enabling HR transformations. In this session learn about the overall integration strategy and vision for Oracle HCM Cloud. This session explores several common integration challenges and how to solve them using Oracle Cloud Platform and the integration capabilities built into Oracle HCM Cloud.
abstract.81: Approaches to learning and training are quickly becoming a strategic way for organizations to better manage and support their employee populations. Whether onboarding, continuous training opportunities, learning from peers, or mandated compliance training, organizations are finding success incorporating modern technology to support the needs of their people. This session explores current trends in modern learning efforts, and examines Oracle’s product vision and strategy over the next couple of years in this space.
abstract.82: APIs have become a mission-critical  part of business. In today’s world it’s essential for your organization to deliver the right APIs as efficiently as possible. In this session learn about the API lifecycle and how to use tooling to scale your development and Ops processes. Hear about exciting new features coming to Apiary and Oracle API Platform Cloud Service, as well as future directions and roadmap.
abstract.83: Demand-side management (DSM) has proven to be an integral component of the utility portfolio and is increasingly important in an evolving landscape that values distributed energy resources (DERs) alongside more traditional assets. This session explores the tremendous potential in connecting grid-side and customer-side resources in an integrated platform, and provides a framework for utilities that are looking to successfully manage DSM programs within that ecosystem.
abstract.84: Oracle Manufacturing Cloud has been successfully deployed by companies around the world. Oracle Supply Chain Management Cloud and Oracle Manufacturing Cloud provide the most complete and comprehensive solution available in the cloud. This session addresses the benefits available to manufacturing companies. Get an update on current capabilities and the future roadmap and hear a manufacturing organization success story.
abstract.85: Welcome to the “new fulfillment economy.” It’s a multichannel world where manufacturers, wholesalers, retailers, and 3PLs have to be ready and able to fulfill orders along any point of the supply chain. Oracle Warehouse Management Cloud Service, built for today’s new fulfillment economy, enables organizations to rapidly deploy a modern WMS solution in a cost-effective manner to increase revenue and improve fulfillment operations. Oracle Inventory Management Cloud Service provides inventory execution in less-complex locations and acts as a hub for Oracle Warehouse Management Cloud Service, enabling costing, supply and financial orchestration, and inventory visibility for broader supply chain business flows. Join this session to learn about the latest updates and product roadmap.
abstract.86: For your business to grow and succeed now and in the future, your order management solution will need to deliver predictive and prescriptive automated order-to-cash processes even if you have a mixture of disparate order capture and fulfillment execution systems.  This session explores how Oracle Order Management Cloud Service provides automation across the digital supply chain for order to cash. The session also examines future product enhancements including how emerging technologies such as chatbots, AI, and Blockchain can enable Industry 4.0 to increase automation intelligence, offer new opportunities for process innovation, and empower order management users.
abstract.87: Looking to transform your planning processes and enable a digital supply chain? Oracle Supply Chain Planning Cloud can take you there. In this session get an overview and see customer deployments of demand management, sales and operations planning, supply planning, and collaboration in the cloud and learn about the new capabilities in the solution. The session also includes sneak previews of how Oracle is embedding machine learning and other disruptive technologies throughout the suite. Through demonstrations and case studies, learn how to achieve tomorrow's supply chain today.
abstract.88: The best transportation and global trade cloud solution continues to innovate and improve. In this session learn about current business drivers, see the current and future go-to-market strategy, and get a sneak peek at the roadmap of Oracle Transportation and Global Trade Management Additional Storage Cloud Service. Learn about advances to existing capabilities and expansion to new areas such as trade agreements and logistics network modeling. Learn how disruptive technologies such as IoT, AI, chatbots, and Blockchain are being incorporated to help you manage your global supply chain efficiently and keep on top of regulatory needs.
abstract.89: Oracle JavaScript Extension Toolkit is Oracle's official JavaScript technology stack, letting you create modern user interfaces for mobile and web applications. Recently, the focus in Oracle JavaScript Extension Toolkit has increasingly been on the W3C Web Component specification, expressed as Oracle's composite component architecture. This new development, as well as a range of new features, is the focus in this session, in addition to a discussion of where Oracle JavaScript Extension Toolkit is going and what you can expect from Oracle JavaScript Extension Toolkit in the coming years.
abstract.90: Gain insight into the investments and product strategy that will shape the future for sales and service.
